 {"id": "franken_networkx-bfignoreweight", "title": "REVIEW: [CRITICAL] bellman_ford family silently ignored edge weights (same class as dijkstra bug)", "description": "single_source_bellman_ford, single_source_bellman_ford_path_length, all_pairs_bellman_ford_path*, and _raw_single_source_bellman_ford all returned hop-count distances on weighted input instead of weighted distances \u2014 the same bug class as br-dijkignoreweight. On path_graph(5) with every edge weight=2.5, fnx returned {0:0, 1:1.0, 2:2.0, 3:3.0, 4:4.0} where nx returns {0:0, 1:2.5, 2:5.0, 3:7.5, 4:10.0}. Added _graph_has_nonunit_weight check to all five wrappers + bidirectional_dijkstra; delegate to nx when any edge has non-unit weight. Verified all now match nx exactly.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-25T01:30:00.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T01:30:00.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-25T01:30:00.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Delegate weighted inputs to nx across BF family", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-fwignoreweight", "title": "REVIEW: [CRITICAL] floyd_warshall and floyd_warshall_predecessor_and_distance ignored edge weights", "description": "Same bug class as br-dijkignoreweight. floyd_warshall and floyd_warshall_predecessor_and_distance returned hop-counts in their all-pairs distance dicts on weighted input. On path_graph(5) with weight=2.5, floyd_warshall[0][4] returned 4.0 where nx returns 10.0. Added _graph_has_nonunit_weight check to both wrappers; delegate weighted inputs to nx. Unweighted fast path preserved.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-25T01:30:00.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T01:30:00.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-25T01:30:00.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Delegate weighted inputs to nx", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-astarignoreweight", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] astar_path and astar_path_length ignored edge weights", "description": "Same bug class as dijkstra / BF / FW: the Rust _raw_astar_path* returned hop-count distances on weighted input. On path_graph(5) with weight=2.5, astar_path_length(0, 4) returned 4.0 where nx returns 10.0. Added _graph_has_nonunit_weight check; delegate weighted inputs to nx. Unit-weight fast path preserved; heuristic kwarg unchanged.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-25T01:30:00.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T01:30:00.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-25T01:30:00.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Delegate weighted inputs to nx", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-coremg", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] core_number + k_core family accepted MultiGraph silently; nx raises NetworkXNotImplemented", "description": "nx.core_number, k_core, k_shell, k_crust, k_corona, and k_truss are all @not_implemented_for('multigraph') and raise NetworkXNotImplemented. The Rust core_number binding and the fnx k_* wrappers silently accepted MultiGraph input and returned a bogus-but-plausible result (e.g. core_number on MG([(0,1),(0,1),(1,2)]) returned {0:1, 1:1, 2:1} treating parallel edges as a single edge). Added is_multigraph guards to all six functions; k_truss also gets directed-rejection. Matches nx's NetworkXNotImplemented exception type + message.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-25T02:00:00.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T02:00:00.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-25T02:00:00.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Python-side is_multigraph guards + is_directed for k_truss", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
